  "prompt": "How do I create date picker in Android like Google calendar?",
  "response": "Creating a date picker in Android similar to the one used in Google Calendar involves using the `DatePickerDialog` or customizing it further if needed. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide to creating a simple date picker:\n\n1. **Add the XML Layout**: First, create a simple layout that includes a button to trigger the date picker dialog.\n\n```xml\n<!-- res/layout/activity_main.xml -->\n<RelativeLayout xmlns:android=\"http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android\"\n    android:layout_width=\"match_parent\"\n    android:layout_height=\"match_parent\">\n\n    <Button\n        android:id=\"@+id/btn_show_date_picker\"\n        android:layout_width=\"wrap_content\"\n        android:layout_height=\"wrap_content\"\n        android:text=\"Show Date Picker\"\n        android:layout_centerInParent=\"true\"/>\n    \n    <TextView\n        android:id=\"@+id/tv_selected_date\"\n        android:layout_width=\"wrap_content\"\n        android:layout_height=\"wrap_content\"\n        android:text=\"Selected Date\"\n        android:layout_below=\"@id/btn_show_date_picker\"\n        android:layout_marginTop=\"20dp\"\n        android:layout_centerHorizontal=\"true\"/>\n</RelativeLayout>\n```\n\n2. **Initialize in MainActivity**: In your `MainActivity.java` or `MainActivity.kt`, initialize the button and set an `OnClickListener` to display the `DatePickerDialog`.\n\n```java\n// MainActivity.java\nimport android.app.DatePickerDialog;\nimport android.os.Bundle;\nimport android.widget.Button;\nimport android.widget.DatePicker;\nimport android.widget.TextView;\nimport androidx.appcompat.app.AppCompatActivity;\nimport java.util.Calendar;\n\npublic class MainActivity extends AppCompatActivity {\n\n    private Button btnShowDatePicker;\n    private TextView tvSelectedDate;\n\n    @Override\n    protected void onCreate(Bundle savedInstanceState) {\n        super.onCreate(savedInstanceState);\n        setContentView(R.layout.activity_main);\n\n        btnShowDatePicker = findViewById(R.id.btn_show_date_picker);\n        tvSelectedDate = findViewById(R.id.tv_selected_date);\n\n        btnShowDatePicker.setOnClickListener(view -> {\n            // Get current date\n            Calendar calendar = Calendar.getInstance();\n            int year = calendar.get(Calendar.YEAR);\n            int month = calendar.get(Calendar.MONTH);\n            int day = calendar.get(Calendar.DAY_OF_MONTH);\n\n            DatePickerDialog datePickerDialog = new DatePickerDialog(MainActivity.this,\n                    new DatePickerDialog.OnDateSetListener() {\n                        @Override\n                        public void onDateSet(DatePicker view, int year, int month, int dayOfMonth) {\n                            // Format the date set by the user\n                            String selectedDate = dayOfMonth + \"/\" + (month + 1) + \"/\" + year;\n                            tvSelectedDate.setText(selectedDate);\n                        }\n                    }, year, month, day);\n            datePickerDialog.show();\n        });\n    }\n}\n```\n\n3. **Customize the Date Picker**: If you want to make the date picker more visually appealing or add custom features like Google Calendar\u2019s, you can further customize it. You might need to build a custom dialog or use third-party libraries.\n\nHere's an example using a library like \"Material DatePicker\":\n\nAdd `MaterialDatePicker` dependency:\n```gradle\nimplementation 'com.google.android.material:material:<latest_version>'\n```\n\nUsage:\n```java\nimport android.os.Bundle;\nimport android.widget.Button;\nimport android.widget.TextView;\nimport androidx.appcompat.app.AppCompatActivity;\nimport com.google.android.material.datepicker.MaterialDatePicker;\n\npublic class MainActivity extends AppCompatActivity {\n    private Button btnShowDatePicker;\n    private TextView tvSelectedDate;\n\n    @Override\n    protected void onCreate(Bundle savedInstanceState) {\n        super.onCreate(savedInstanceState);\n        setContentView(R.layout.activity_main);\n\n        btnShowDatePicker = findViewById(R.id.btn_show_date_picker);\n        tvSelectedDate = findViewById(R.id.tv_selected_date);\n\n        btnShowDatePicker.setOnClickListener(view -> {\n            MaterialDatePicker.Builder<Long> builder = MaterialDatePicker.Builder.datePicker();\n            MaterialDatePicker<Long> picker = builder.build();\n            \n            picker.addOnPositiveButtonClickListener(selection -> {\n                tvSelectedDate.setText(picker.getHeaderText());\n            });\n\n            picker.show(getSupportFragmentManager(), picker.toString());\n        });\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Summary:\n- **Basic Date Picker**: Use `DatePickerDialog`.\n- **Advanced Custom Date Picker**: Use libraries like Google\u2019s Material Date Picker.\n  \nChoose depending on how close you want it to resemble Google Calendar\u2019s date picker and other specific needs.",
